{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":800,"text":"15 years ago, I volunteered\nto participate in a research study"},{"time":6080,"text":"that involved a genetic test."},{"time":8640,"text":"When I arrived at the clinic to be tested,"},{"time":10672,"text":"I was handed a questionnaire."},{"time":13080,"text":"One of the very first questions\nasked me to check a box for my race:"},{"time":17320,"text":"White, black, Asian, or Native American."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21680,"text":"I wasn't quite sure\nhow to answer the question."},{"time":25200,"text":"Was it aimed at measuring the diversity"},{"time":27600,"text":"of research participants'\nsocial backgrounds?"},{"time":31200,"text":"In that case, I would answer\nwith my social identity,"},{"time":34840,"text":"and check the box for \"black.\""},{"time":37480,"text":"But what if the researchers\nwere interested in investigating"},{"time":41040,"text":"some association between ancestry\nand the risk for certain genetic traits?"},{"time":47160,"text":"In that case, wouldn't they want to know\nsomething about my ancestry,"},{"time":51720,"text":"which is just as much European as African?"},{"time":55000,"text":"And how could they make\nscientific findings about my genes"},{"time":59640,"text":"if I put down my social identity\nas a black woman?"},{"time":64480,"text":"After all, I consider myself\na black woman with a white father"},{"time":69640,"text":"rather than a white woman\nwith a black mother"},{"time":73080,"text":"entirely for social reasons."},{"time":75800,"text":"Which racial identity I check"},{"time":78280,"text":"has nothing to do with my genes."},{"time":82080,"text":"Well, despite the obvious\nimportance of this question"},{"time":85480,"text":"to the study's scientific validity,"},{"time":88000,"text":"I was told, \"Don't worry about it,"},{"time":90560,"text":"just put down however\nyou identify yourself.\""},{"time":94200,"text":"So I check \"black,\""},{"time":96600,"text":"but I had no confidence\nin the results of a study"},{"time":100320,"text":"that treated a critical variable\nso unscientifically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106360,"text":"That personal experience\nwith the use of race in genetic testing"},{"time":110720,"text":"got me thinking:"},{"time":112320,"text":"Where else in medicine is race used\nto make false biological predictions?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":118720,"text":"Well, I found out that race runs deeply\nthroughout all of medical practice."},{"time":125000,"text":"It shapes physicians' diagnoses,"},{"time":128039,"text":"measurements, treatments,"},{"time":130680,"text":"prescriptions,"},{"time":132320,"text":"even the very definition of diseases."},{"time":136400,"text":"And the more I found out,\nthe more disturbed I became."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141720,"text":"Sociologists like me have long explained"},{"time":144840,"text":"that race is a social construction."},{"time":147760,"text":"When we identify people as black,\nwhite, Asian, Native American, Latina,"},{"time":154280,"text":"we're referring to social groupings"},{"time":157040,"text":"with made up demarcations\nthat have changed over time"},{"time":160760,"text":"and vary around the world."},{"time":163320,"text":"As a legal scholar, I've also studied"},{"time":166560,"text":"how lawmakers, not biologists,"},{"time":169000,"text":"have invented the legal\ndefinitions of races."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174640,"text":"And it's not just the view\nof social scientists."},{"time":178120,"text":"You remember when the map\nof the human genome"},{"time":180760,"text":"was unveiled at a White House\nceremony in June 2000?"},{"time":185040,"text":"President Bill Clinton famously declared,"},{"time":188680,"text":"\"I believe one of the great truths"},{"time":190880,"text":"to emerge from this triumphant expedition"},{"time":194080,"text":"inside the human genome"},{"time":195920,"text":"is that in genetic terms,"},{"time":197800,"text":"human beings, regardless of race,"},{"time":200640,"text":"are more than 99.9 percent the same.\""},{"time":204920,"text":"And he might have added"},{"time":206520,"text":"that that less than one percent\nof genetic difference"},{"time":210240,"text":"doesn't fall into racial boxes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213440,"text":"Francis Collins, who led\nthe Human Genome Project"},{"time":217120,"text":"and now heads NIH,"},{"time":218840,"text":"echoed President Clinton."},{"time":220920,"text":"\"I am happy that today,"},{"time":222880,"text":"the only race we're talking about\nis the human race.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":228400,"text":"Doctors are supposed to practice\nevidence-based medicine,"},{"time":232400,"text":"and they're increasingly called\nto join the genomic revolution."},{"time":236360,"text":"But their habit of treating patients\nby race lags far behind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242200,"text":"Take the estimate"},{"time":243440,"text":"of glomerular filtration rate, or GFR."},{"time":246720,"text":"Doctors routinely interpret GFR,"},{"time":250280,"text":"this important indicator\nof kidney function, by race."},{"time":255840,"text":"As you can see in this lab test,"},{"time":259720,"text":"the exact same creatinine level,"},{"time":264920,"text":"the concentration\nin the blood of the patient,"},{"time":268720,"text":"automatically produces\na different GFR estimate"},{"time":273200,"text":"depending on whether or not\nthe patient is African-American."},{"time":279120,"text":"Why?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":281280,"text":"I've been told it's based on an assumption"},{"time":284560,"text":"that African-Americans\nhave more muscle mass"},{"time":287680,"text":"than people of other races."},{"time":290880,"text":"But what sense does it make"},{"time":292720,"text":"for a doctor to automatically assume"},{"time":296200,"text":"I have more muscle mass\nthan that female bodybuilder?"},{"time":300600,"text":"Wouldn't it be far more accurate\nand evidence-based"},{"time":304600,"text":"to determine the muscle mass\nof individual patients"},{"time":308640,"text":"just by looking at them?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":312360,"text":"Well, doctors tell me\nthey're using race as a shortcut."},{"time":315800,"text":"It's a crude but convenient proxy"},{"time":318560,"text":"for more important factors,\nlike muscle mass,"},{"time":321840,"text":"enzyme level, genetic traits"},{"time":324240,"text":"they just don't have time to look for."},{"time":327600,"text":"But race is a bad proxy."},{"time":330400,"text":"In many cases, race adds\nno relevant information at all."},{"time":334560,"text":"It's just a distraction."},{"time":337600,"text":"But race also tends to overwhelm\nthe clinical measures."},{"time":343440,"text":"It blinds doctors to patients' symptoms,"},{"time":347760,"text":"family illnesses,"},{"time":350440,"text":"their history, their own illnesses\nthey might have --"},{"time":354800,"text":"all more evidence-based\nthan the patient's race."},{"time":359920,"text":"Race can't substitute\nfor these important clinical measures"},{"time":364720,"text":"without sacrificing patient well-being."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369800,"text":"Doctors also tell me\nrace is just one of many factors"},{"time":373480,"text":"they take into account,"},{"time":375040,"text":"but there are numerous medical tests,"},{"time":377200,"text":"like the GFR,"},{"time":378960,"text":"that use race categorically"},{"time":382240,"text":"to treat black, white,\nAsian patients differently"},{"time":386240,"text":"just because of their race."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389680,"text":"Race medicine also leaves\npatients of color especially vulnerable"},{"time":395200,"text":"to harmful biases and stereotypes."},{"time":398600,"text":"Black and Latino patients\nare twice as likely"},{"time":401920,"text":"to receive no pain medication as whites"},{"time":405440,"text":"for the same painful long bone fractures"},{"time":410040,"text":"because of stereotypes"},{"time":412280,"text":"that black and brown people\nfeel less pain,"},{"time":416160,"text":"exaggerate their pain,"},{"time":418120,"text":"and are predisposed to drug addiction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422320,"text":"The Food and Drug Administration has even\napproved a race-specific medicine."},{"time":428000,"text":"It's a pill called BiDil"},{"time":430440,"text":"to treat heart failure in self-identified\nAfrican-American patients."},{"time":435640,"text":"A cardiologist developed this drug\nwithout regard to race or genetics,"},{"time":441840,"text":"but it became convenient"},{"time":444120,"text":"for commercial reasons"},{"time":446040,"text":"to market the drug to black patients."},{"time":450360,"text":"The FDA then allowed"},{"time":452640,"text":"the company, the drug company,"},{"time":455720,"text":"to test the efficacy in a clinical trial"},{"time":459360,"text":"that only included\nAfrican-American subjects."},{"time":464760,"text":"It speculated"},{"time":466560,"text":"that race stood in as a proxy\nfor some unknown genetic factor"},{"time":472680,"text":"that affects heart disease"},{"time":475480,"text":"or response to drugs."},{"time":479560,"text":"But think about\nthe dangerous message it sent,"},{"time":483040,"text":"that black people's bodies\nare so substandard,"},{"time":487520,"text":"a drug tested in them"},{"time":489240,"text":"is not guaranteed\nto work in other patients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494840,"text":"In the end, the drug company's\nmarketing scheme failed."},{"time":498680,"text":"For one thing, black patients\nwere understandably wary"},{"time":502680,"text":"of using a drug just for black people."},{"time":506080,"text":"One elderly black woman stood up\nin a community meeting and shouted,"},{"time":510040,"text":"\"Give me what the white\npeople are taking!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":512520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":515559,"text":"And if you find race-specific\nmedicine surprising,"},{"time":520200,"text":"wait until you learn"},{"time":522159,"text":"that many doctors in the United States"},{"time":525000,"text":"still use an updated version"},{"time":528160,"text":"of a diagnostic tool"},{"time":530080,"text":"that was developed by a physician\nduring the slavery era,"},{"time":534560,"text":"a diagnostic tool that is tightly linked"},{"time":537880,"text":"to justifications for slavery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541560,"text":"Dr. Samuel Cartwright graduated"},{"time":544240,"text":"from the University\nof Pennsylvania Medical School."},{"time":547640,"text":"He practiced in the Deep South\nbefore the Civil War,"},{"time":551240,"text":"and he was a well-known expert\non what was then called \"Negro medicine.\""},{"time":556120,"text":"He promoted the racial concept of disease,"},{"time":559360,"text":"that people of different races\nsuffer from different diseases"},{"time":563080,"text":"and experience\ncommon diseases differently."},{"time":567880,"text":"Cartwright argued in the 1850s"},{"time":571160,"text":"that slavery was beneficial\nfor black people"},{"time":575200,"text":"for medical reasons."},{"time":577280,"text":"He claimed that because black people\nhave lower lung capacity than whites,"},{"time":582200,"text":"forced labor was good for them."},{"time":585840,"text":"He wrote in a medical journal,"},{"time":588120,"text":"\"It is the red vital blood\nsent to the brain"},{"time":591560,"text":"that liberates their minds\nwhen under the white man's control,"},{"time":595920,"text":"and it is the want of sufficiency\nof red vital blood"},{"time":599680,"text":"that chains their minds to ignorance\nand barbarism when in freedom.\""},{"time":605160,"text":"To support this theory,\nCartwright helped to perfect"},{"time":608320,"text":"a medical device for measuring breathing\ncalled the spirometer"},{"time":614240,"text":"to show the presumed deficiency\nin black people's lungs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619880,"text":"Today, doctors still\nuphold Cartwright's claim"},{"time":625440,"text":"the black people as a race"},{"time":628080,"text":"have lower lung capacity\nthan white people."},{"time":632280,"text":"Some even use a modern day spirometer"},{"time":636600,"text":"that actually has a button labeled \"race\""},{"time":640360,"text":"so the machine adjusts the measurement"},{"time":643040,"text":"for each patient\naccording to his or her race."},{"time":647040,"text":"It's a well-known function\ncalled \"correcting for race.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":653880,"text":"The problem with race medicine\nextends far beyond misdiagnosing patients."},{"time":659920,"text":"Its focus on innate\nracial differences in disease"},{"time":664400,"text":"diverts attention and resources"},{"time":667520,"text":"from the social determinants"},{"time":669760,"text":"that cause appalling\nracial gaps in health:"},{"time":673760,"text":"lack of access\nto high-quality medical care;"},{"time":677560,"text":"food deserts in poor neighborhoods;"},{"time":681160,"text":"exposure to environmental toxins;"},{"time":685000,"text":"high rates of incarceration;"},{"time":687920,"text":"and experiencing the stress\nof racial discrimination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693120,"text":"You see, race is not a biological category"},{"time":696920,"text":"that naturally produces\nthese health disparities"},{"time":700360,"text":"because of genetic difference."},{"time":703240,"text":"Race is a social category"},{"time":705880,"text":"that has staggering\nbiological consequences,"},{"time":709560,"text":"but because of the impact\nof social inequality on people's health."},{"time":715160,"text":"Yet race medicine pretends\nthe answer to these gaps in health"},{"time":719320,"text":"can be found in a race-specific pill."},{"time":722560,"text":"It's much easier and more lucrative"},{"time":725320,"text":"to market a technological fix"},{"time":728680,"text":"for these gaps in health"},{"time":730840,"text":"than to deal with the structural\ninequities that produce them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737960,"text":"The reason I'm so passionate\nabout ending race medicine"},{"time":742320,"text":"isn't just because it's bad medicine."},{"time":745400,"text":"I'm also on this mission"},{"time":747280,"text":"because the way doctors practice medicine"},{"time":750240,"text":"continues to promote\na false and toxic view of humanity."},{"time":756840,"text":"Despite the many visionary breakthroughs\nin medicine we've been learning about,"},{"time":762960,"text":"there's a failure of imagination"},{"time":765600,"text":"when it comes to race."},{"time":768920,"text":"Would you imagine with me, just a moment:"},{"time":772600,"text":"What would happen if doctors\nstopped treating patients by race?"},{"time":780360,"text":"Suppose they rejected"},{"time":782920,"text":"an 18th-century classification system"},{"time":786640,"text":"and incorporated instead\nthe most advanced knowledge"},{"time":790400,"text":"of human genetic diversity and unity,"},{"time":793360,"text":"that human beings cannot be categorized\ninto biological races?"},{"time":800600,"text":"What if, instead of using race\nas a crude proxy"},{"time":805400,"text":"for some more important factor,"},{"time":807800,"text":"doctors actually investigated\nand addressed that more important factor?"},{"time":814720,"text":"What if doctors joined the forefront"},{"time":817880,"text":"of a movement to end\nthe structural inequities"},{"time":821640,"text":"caused by racism,"},{"time":823880,"text":"not by genetic difference?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":829240,"text":"Race medicine is bad medicine,"},{"time":833160,"text":"it's poor science"},{"time":835320,"text":"and it's a false\ninterpretation of humanity."},{"time":839520,"text":"It is more urgent than ever"},{"time":842120,"text":"to finally abandon this backward legacy"},{"time":846680,"text":"and to affirm our common humanity"},{"time":850120,"text":"by ending the social inequalities\nthat truly divide us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856040,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":857280,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":859520,"text":"Thank you. Thanks."},{"time":862320,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}